*IDENT    CHAA311
*BEFORE   HISTORY.2 
 CHAA311  PROBLEM - DATES ARE NOT DISPLAYED CORRECTLY BY *NLTERM* IF
          THE YEAR IS BEYOND 1999.
  
          SOLUTION - CORRECT BINARY-TO-DISPLAY CODE CONVERSION
          OF DATE TO ACCOUNT FOR YEAR 2000.
  
          PCS.   98/09/25.   NLTZLST
*COMPILE  HISTORY
*INSERT   NLTZLST.150
      ITEM YEAR    U;                  # CURRENT YEAR (FROM *CATLIST*) #
*DELETE   NLTZLST.317,NLTZLST.321
            YEAR = B<00,06>ENTDATM[0] + 70;
                                       # ADD BASE YEAR OFFSET (1970).  #
            IF YEAR GQ 100 THEN YEAR = YEAR - 100;
                                       # ADJUST FOR YEAR 2000.         #
            C<0,2>CATLISTDATE[CNDX] = NLT$CDE(YEAR, 2);
*COMPILE  NLTZLST                      # CONVERT YEAR TO DISPLAY CODE. #
*/ THERE ARE     20 CORRECTION CARDS INCLUDING THIS COMMENT.
